text.section:
Except as provided in subsection (d) of this section, when, in connection with a real estate transaction that involves a purchase money mortgage or deed of trust on land in the State, a title insurer accepts a premium for a policy that insures the title to the property or the title insurer, its agent, or employee accepts a premium for mortgagee title insurance, the person first accepting the premium:
shall insert the name of each insured in the binder for the title insurance or the title report; and
immediately on receipt of the premium, shall deliver to the buyer or agent or attorney of the buyer written notice:
of the name of each insured under the policy;
of the face amount of the policy;
of the buyer's right and opportunity to obtain simultaneous title insurance in the buyer's favor;
of the additional premium that will be required for purchase of simultaneous title insurance in the buyer's favor;
that the buyer's title insurance will be subject only to the contingencies and conditions contained in the binder, title report, and policy;
of the buyer's right to review a sample of the form of policy in which the contingencies and conditions will be inserted; and
that contains a clear statement of the contingencies that must be satisfied to make the buyer's policy effective, if the buyer's policy is not effective on payment of the premium.
